window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Maddie Whittle can't let go of the past.</p> <p>Life hasn't been the same since she lost her brother six years ago. She keeps the grief boxed away, instead focusing on turning her family's estate into a recovery retreat.</p> <p>So the last thing Maddie expects — or wants — is James Byron, a former schoolmate, showing up at her home in search of a runaway pig.</p> <p>He's infuriating, stubborn and a walking contradiction — a man who has no time for Maddie yet refuses to turn his back on the scruffy rescue dog who follows him everywhere.</p> <p>But she needs help. And he needs a job.</p> <p>The only thing they can agree on is their mutual dislike as they find themselves embarking on a winter of renovation, working side by side.</p> <p>But against her better judgement, and the fact they couldn't be more different, Maddie finds herself drawn to James more than anyone she's ever met.</p> <p>Maddie and James are entangled in something neither of them expected — an unspoken connection, a spark of something real.</p> <p>Maddie has been living life in her brother's memory. Can she find the courage to open her heart and live it to the full . . . this time, for herself?</p> <p><b>From an award-winning author, this is a heartwarming story about finding love — or it finding you — in the most unexpected places. Perfect for fans of Cecilia Ahern, Nicholas Sparks, Shari Low, Amanda Prowse, Jojo Moyes or Holly Miller.</b></p>"; 
